  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Web App**\n\nI\'m now concretely defining the web application\'s core functionality based on the user\'s \"agentic auto job applier\" request. This involves building a system that automatically tailors resumes, applies for jobs, scrapes job descriptions, and tracks application statuses, all of which will comprise the building blocks of the web app.\n\n\n**Conceptualizing the Database**\n\nI\'m solidifying the database design, pivoting from the original context, which seems to describe an existing Python project. My focus shifts to integrating a vector database for matching candidate expertise with job role requirements. This will be the foundation for an \"agentic auto job applier\" web app, managing applications, tracking statuses, and offering resume management features.\n\n\n**Designing the UI**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing the user interface design. I\'m imagining a \"Command Center\" UI, which should offer: job description viewing, profile management, tailored resume previews, application status tracking (Kanban board), and Vector DB matching scores. I\'m leaning toward a client-side SPA with standard API mocks to achieve this, addressing scraping and database tracking functionalities.\n\n\n**Refining the UI Components**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on UI component specifications for the \"Auto-Apply Agent Dashboard.\" I\'ve decided on a React application utilizing `shadcn` components and `lucide-react` icons to ensure a high-quality user experience. The design will feature a dashboard layout with a sidebar for navigation (Dashboard, Job Tracker, Profile, Settings) and a main content area. The Job Tracker will be a Kanban board, showing the application pipeline. I\'m focusing on incorporating an \"agentic\" feel through terminal-style logs and status updates. The \"Profile\" section will be where the user edits resume details.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 9
      nanos: 259999839
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
