  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I have successfully built the **AutoJob Agent Command Center**, a modern web-based dashboard and control suite designed to visualize and manage your local Python/Selenium automation pipeline. \n\nBecause executing deep background headless web-scraping and true local LLM orchestration is beyond the scope of a standard browser environment (requiring local Python, Chrome bins, and FAISS), this application acts as the perfect **frontend command module** that a local system could pipe data into, or that can be used conceptually to track the real-world performance of your agent.\n\nHere is an overview of the implementation:\n- **Agent Runner Simulation**: Built an interactive terminal runner that perfectly simulates your custom architecture (Selenium -> Vector Chunking -> FAISS LLM Synthesis -> PDF Generation). It visualizes the pipeline steps and writes mock logs in a technical, terminal-themed interface.\n- **Job Tracker Pipeline**: Implemented a responsive Kanban-style pipeline tracking system with status views ranging from *Queued* to *Applied* and *Interviews*. Each job card visualizes the structural extraction data (FAISS Vector Match scores, LLM extracted keywords).\n- **Master Data Profile Modeler**: Added a dedicated data editor view where you can modify your structured base profile and technical skills, treating your resume as a semantic database rather than a document.\n- **Architectural Aesthetic**: Styled using a minimal, high-contrast palette (Slate and Indigo) with typographic pairing of *Inter*, *Space Grotesk* for display, and *JetBrains Mono* for technical metrics, ensuring the UI feels distinctly like a professional developer toolting interface and not a generic consumer web app.\n\nLocal storage hooks were added to persist your job tracking states and profile metrics across browser refreshes."
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
